  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this clinical study was to evaluate whether vaginal tablets containing 10 mg
      dequalinium chloride (Fluomizin) are comparable in clinical efficacy and safety to
      clindamycin vaginal cream (2%) in patients suffering from bacterial vaginosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      An international, multi-center, single-blind, randomized, active-controlled study with two
      parallel groups in patients with bacterial vaginosis. Eligible patients were randomized to
      receive Fluomizin vaginal tablets for 6 days or Clindamycin vaginal cream (2%) for 7 days.
      Control examinations were performed 3 to 14 days and 2 to 6 weeks after the end of the
      therapy.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
