  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of bacterial vaginosis

          -  Women aged 18-55 years

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy or lactation

          -  Uterine bleeding (including menstruation but not including cervical contact bleeding
             on sampling) or vaginal bleeding of unknown origin

          -  Acute infections of the upper genital tract

          -  Clinical Symptoms of a vulvovaginal Candidiasis

          -  Use of anti-infectives (local or systemic) in the previous 14 days and/or during the
             study
      </textblock>
